From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ondrej Jirman <megi@xff.cz>
Date: Wed, 11 Feb 2026 03:48:27 +0100
Subject: clk: sunxi-ng: Shorten wait time for PLL lock

Time to lock is usually 250 us for CPUX PLL. Polling in increments of
100us increases the waiting time by 50 us for little reason.

Signed-off-by: Ondrej Jirman <megi@xff.cz>
---
 drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu_common.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu_common.c b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu_common.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu_common.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu_common.c
@@ -35,7 +35,7 @@ void ccu_helper_wait_for_lock(struct ccu_common *common, u32 lock)
 	else
 		addr = common->base + common->reg;
 
-	WARN_ON(readl_relaxed_poll_timeout(addr, reg, reg & lock, 100, 70000));
+	WARN_ON(readl_relaxed_poll_timeout(addr, reg, reg & lock, 25, 70000));
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_NS_GPL(ccu_helper_wait_for_lock, "SUNXI_CCU");
 
-- 
Armbian

